Anatomy. Digestive system . The jaws are triangularly ovoid ( Fig. 5G ) The masticatory processes of the jaws bear a single row of low, barely conspicuous denticles ( Fig. 5H ). The radular formula in the holotype is 27 x 0.1.0. The radular teeth are yellowish. The central tooth is narrow, elongated, with low cusp and 5–8 lateral denticles, including few intercalating smaller denticles, commonly at central cusp of some teeth (
Fig. 5I , J, K
).

Distribution
. NW Аtlantic (
USА
) to White Sea (
Russia
).
